Key Match Events: The Cleveland Cavaliers handed the Golden State Warriors their 16th loss of the season with a 113-95 blowout win.
Donovan Mitchell and Darius Garland combined for a 48-point outing.
Stephen Curry was held to just 11 points in 29 minutes.
Pre-Game Insights: The Golden State Warriors entered the game with a 16-15 record and were looking to get their season back on track.
The Warriors had not been performing well since acquiring Dennis Schröder via trade with the Brooklyn Nets.
Post-Match Reflections: Steve Kerr stated, 'You are what your record says you are. I think there's a lot of truth to that. We've fallen from that early start where we had a lot of momentum and good flow to our game.'
